# =============================================================================
# Asperitas CODEOWNERS v2
# =============================================================================
#
# Purpose:
# - require explicit ownership for repository governance, source provenance,
#   biological evidence, compliance, evaluation, packaging, CI, and runtime
#   control surfaces;
# - keep a repository-wide fallback owner so newly introduced files do not
#   silently become ownerless;
# - make sensitive ownership boundaries visible before future team delegation.
#
# Current canonical owner:
#   @neo6bs988-dev
#
# Enforcement boundary:
# - CODEOWNERS identifies requested reviewers.
# - Mandatory approval requires a GitHub branch ruleset or branch-protection
#   rule that requires review from Code Owners.
# - Ownership does not itself prove security, correctness, rights clearance,
#   scientific validation, deployment, or production readiness.
#
# Pattern-order rule:
# - GitHub applies the last matching CODEOWNERS pattern.
# - The repository-wide fallback appears first.
# - More specific sensitive paths appear later.
# =============================================================================


